My motherhood journey after infertility and miscarriage ❤️

This is me replaying the last 3 years of being a mom, because the journey to motherhood was not an easy one for us. It took two years of being unable to conceive, to finally getting that first positive pregnancy test which ended in a miscarriage only six weeks later. Being a mom is something I longed for so long and we just knew it would happen for us one day 🤍 Enter Aleah, my first, my sunshine, the girl who was worth such a long wait. Thank you God for bringing us this miracle that we prayed so long and hard for. She’s so grown now, she’s flourishing and she’ll put a smile on the face of everyone around her. Just like she does for her new baby sister, Naomi. Naomi, my little surprise. The one who was so eager to come into this world that she came so quick! You’re the sweetest child, the most smiley baby and we see all the best parts of us in you. Our little family, we’ve longed for you so much and I’m in tears as I write this because I cant believe this is now my reality. 

To all of you watching, if you’re already a mom I’m so proud of you. Proud of your selflessness and proud of your dedication to them. Motherhood is not easy by any means but just know you’re the best mom they can have and you’re doing such an amazing job ❤️

To those of you expecting to be a mom, however your child becomes a part of your family I’m so excited for you. I pray this new journey will give you so much joy and fulfillment. And I just can’t wait for you to meet your little best friend 🫶🏼

And to all of you longing to be a mom, or a mom to another. I see you, I feel for you and I pray that it should happen for you so soon. The wait can be painful, discouraging and at times hopeless. But let me be the one to tell you that when it does happen, and it will (however it does) all that time and emotion you felt waiting… it’ll be gone in a snap. And that hole in your heart will be bursting with more love then you can imagine. 

To all the mama’s now, then and to come, Happy Mother’s Day 🌹

Love, a grateful + teary eyed mom ❤️

How to Change ANY Lamp in 3 Steps!💡MS. FIX IT SERIES

PS. This works exactly the same for ceiling lamps too! 

Disclaimer: I am not a professional, just sharing what I know so these projects won’t seem as intimidating as you think to do! 

SAVE FOR LATER so you can impress the man in your life ✨

⚡️MAKE SURE POWER SWITCH IS OFF BEFORE STARTING⚡️
Step 1: Remove the lamp base to get to the electrical 
Step 2: Unscrew the old mount and twist off the orange caps to disconnect the wires, then detach and remove old mount
Step 3: Fish wires through and screw new mount into place, twist both black wires together, then both white wires together and connect by adding an orange nut and turning clockwise
Final step: tuck in wires and attach base to the wall 

*if your light fixture base is made or metal, you will need ti do one more step and ground the copper wire, you can google how to do this, it’s easy!*

If you struggle to give yourself a salon blowout with a brush and blow dryer, this thermal brush makes it so much easier! 

Styling Tips
~ ensure hair is fully dry before styling 
~ use a heat protectant 
~ it’s really important to have NO knots, the brush is made of silicon and can pull on your hair if it isn’t smooth 
~ run through the hair piece once to smooth frizz, then second time to curl 
~ alternate curl directions but ensure top layer is curled away from face 
~ turn iron at ends in constant loop for a more curled end!
